In this Oval Office meeting, President Biden meets with the Congressional Black Caucus (CBC) and Representative Horsford to discuss various topics, including their progress and investments in the African American community, police reform, and violence in communities. The President congratulates Congressman Horsford on his election and acknowledges the recent burial of Tyre Nichols, expressing hope that it will prompt action. He mentions the House passing police reform in 2021 and the executive orders he has implemented. The President emphasizes the deadline for agencies to demonstrate meeting the requirements and expresses his willingness to discuss the details. Representative Horsford thanks the President and Vice President for prioritizing the issue and emphasizes the need for legislative actions to save lives and prioritize public safety. The meeting concludes with a commitment to get to work.